# Korea Auto Market - Tech Stack Rules

Always use:

## Frontend

- Next.js 15 App Router
- TypeScript
- TailwindCSS
- Shadcn UI

## State Management

- Zustand
- TanStack Query

## Database

- PostgreSQL on Vultr VPS
- Drizzle ORM
- `pg` driver (node-postgres)

## Storage

- Cloudflare R2

## Authentication

- Telegram Mini App SDK

## Validation

- Zod

## Deployment

- Vultr VPS
- Docker + Docker Compose
- GitHub Actions (CI/CD only — never manual deploy)
- Nginx (reverse proxy container)
- Let's Encrypt (Certbot)

## Code Quality

- Strict TypeScript
- Reusable components
- Mobile First
- Responsive Design

## Forbidden

- Firebase
- MongoDB
- Prisma
- Redux
- Material UI
- Ant Design
- Express
- NestJS
- Supabase
- Neon
- PM2 (use Docker Compose)
- Manual production deploys

Always follow existing architecture.

Never replace technologies without permission.

Always generate production-ready code.
